The paper investigates the use of game theoretic representations to teach robots new skills, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also combines aspects of learning by demonstration and active learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on human-robot interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's use of game theory to represent and learn how to play interactive games also falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
